snippet.textDisplay:
CS-Pak redoes songs, but also creates original tracks. It depends on the artist, either he brings a new track or an old one, the housebands just adjust to that! Second, you say they pick sufi classics, but you do realise it is well balanced! In every season, in every episode, there are sufi tracks, then there are folk tracks, and then there are the modern rock-pop tracks. 
Bottom line: CS-Pak has it all, and is on a completely different level.

snippet.textDisplay:
Title: Mauje Naina

"You think I'm crazy,
but I'm not.
When I close my eyes,
The lights go off.

Lie awake in my bed,
Your secrets in my head.

you think I'm crazy..
I just point the way,
Watch you go down.
Like a sure refrain,
You come around 

Lie awake, unprepared,
To still the madness in my head

Don’t think I'm crazy,
I'm not!

When I close my eyes
The lights go off!!

Hope people get the real meaning of the song!
